{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Stokes data are generalised monodromy data associated to meromorphic connections with irregular singularities.",
    "Considering them is necessary to obtain an irregular analogue of the famous Riemann-Hilbert correspondence.",
    "The latter gives, on any smooth algebraic variety, an equivalence between connections with regular singularities (the de Rham side) and monodromy data (the Betti side).",
    "Its irregular version, known as the Riemann-Hilbert-Birkhoff correspondence, provides an equivalence between possibly irregular connections and generalised monodromy data.",
    "These generalised monodromy data can be encoded in several different ways, one of them being the notion of Stokes local system ([Boa01, Boa21]), which is closely related to the wild fundamental group of [MR91]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "These generalised monodromy data can be encoded in several different ways, one of them being the notion of Stokes local system ([Boa01, Boa21]), which is closely related to the wild fundamental group of [MR91]."
  ]
}